  , issueCommentBody =
      "You can configure one auth key to access the cluster -- there is no way to set an auth key to be specific to a database or table.\r\n\r\nThe auth key is stored in a system table called `cluster_config`, in the system `rethinkdb` database. You can read more about how system tables are used for cluster administration tasks here: http://rethinkdb.com/docs/system-tables/\r\n\r\nSupposing no auth key has been set, if I run this query to see the contents of the `cluster_config` table:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.db('rethinkdb').table('cluster_config')\r\n```\r\n\r\n...then I can see no auth key has been set.\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n    \"auth_key\": null ,\r\n    \"id\":  \"auth\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnce I've set the auth key (by updating the `auth_key` document):\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.db('rethinkdb').table('cluster_config').update({'auth_key': 'hunter22'})\r\n```\r\n\r\n...the `cluster_config` table will show that a key has been set (but will hide the actual auth key for security purposes):\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n    \"auth_key\": {\r\n        \"hidden\": true\r\n    } ,\r\n    \"id\":  \"auth\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I try to connect to the cluster now (using the default values), I should get an error:\r\n\r\n```py\r\n>>> import rethinkdb as r\r\n>>> r.connect()\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n...\r\nRqlDriverError: Server dropped connection with message: \"ERROR: Incorrect author\r\nization key.\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nUsing the new auth key, I can connect successfully:\r\n\r\n```py\r\n>>> r.connect(auth_key='hunter22')\r\n<rethinkdb.net.Connection object at 0x10f333fd0>\r\n```"
  , issueCommentId = 76207845
